01:02:48.990 --> 01:02:52.580
but the Raman resonance,
capital delta 2,

01:02:52.580 --> 01:02:55.670
means that we are smack
on the single photon

01:02:55.670 --> 01:02:57.500
resonance for the probe laser.

01:02:57.500 --> 01:03:00.405
So this feature is pretty
much we take the ground state

01:03:00.405 --> 01:03:05.010
and go exactly to the excited
state with a single photon.

01:03:05.010 --> 01:03:06.650
There is an AC
Stark shift involved

01:03:06.650 --> 01:03:10.370
but it's not relevant here,
whereas the other feature is

01:03:10.370 --> 01:03:13.680
the two photon Raman feature.

01:03:13.680 --> 01:03:16.520
And the one thing I wanted
to point out in this context

01:03:16.520 --> 01:03:21.390
is that there is
actually a small energy

01:03:21.390 --> 01:03:25.820
splitting between the two photon
Raman feature by the AC Stark

01:03:25.820 --> 01:03:28.510
effect, whereas the
EIT feature always

01:03:28.510 --> 01:03:31.190
happens at Raman
resonance delta equals 0.

01:03:38.500 --> 01:03:42.140
Because, just to
emphasize that, delta

01:03:42.140 --> 01:03:46.570
equals 0 is really you induce
a coherence between g and f.

01:03:46.570 --> 01:03:48.490
It's a dark state,
and when you have

01:03:48.490 --> 01:03:51.390
a dark state in
that situation, you

01:03:51.390 --> 01:03:53.000
don't have an AC Stark effect.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:56.470
So the EIT feature
is at delta equals 0,

01:03:56.470 --> 01:03:59.870
whereas the photon scattering
features, they suffer,

01:03:59.870 --> 01:04:01.870
or they experience--

01:04:01.870 --> 01:04:04.140
it may not be negative to
suffer an AC Stark shift,

01:04:04.140 --> 01:04:05.868
but they experience
an AC Stark shift.

01:04:09.360 --> 01:04:10.140
Further questions?

01:04:10.140 --> 01:04:10.670
Yes?

01:04:10.670 --> 01:04:13.000
STUDENT: Can we
somehow relate this

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:16.740
to Doppler free spectroscopy?

01:04:16.740 --> 01:04:20.990
PROFESSOR: Can we relate that
to Doppler free spectroscopy?

01:04:20.990 --> 01:04:24.760
Actually, I don't
think so because I

01:04:24.760 --> 01:04:28.402
would say for the
whole discussion here,

01:04:28.402 --> 01:04:30.860
let's assume we have an atom
which has infinite mass, which

01:04:30.860 --> 01:04:32.300
is not moving at all.

01:04:32.300 --> 01:04:36.310
We're really talking
about internal coherences.

01:04:36.310 --> 01:04:41.540
However, and that's
where it becomes related,

01:04:41.540 --> 01:04:44.860
if you look at very,
very narrow features

01:04:44.860 --> 01:04:48.320
as a function of detuning
then, of course, Doppler shifts

01:04:48.320 --> 01:04:51.900
play a role, and if you
have very, very, very

01:04:51.900 --> 01:04:56.710
narrow features, you become
sensitive to very, very, very

01:04:56.710 --> 01:04:59.290
small velocities,
and therefore, you

01:04:59.290 --> 01:05:01.950
have an opportunity to cool.

01:05:01.950 --> 01:05:05.080
So if you can distinguish
spectroscopically

01:05:05.080 --> 01:05:07.770
an atom which moves a tiny
little bit and an atom which

01:05:07.770 --> 01:05:10.780
stands still, if you
can, by a narrow line,

01:05:10.780 --> 01:05:12.920
distinguish the two,
then you can actually

01:05:12.920 --> 01:05:15.630
laser cool this atom.

01:05:15.630 --> 01:05:21.170
The EIT feature can give you
extremely high resolution.

01:05:21.170 --> 01:05:23.090
I'm not discussing it here.

01:05:23.090 --> 01:05:25.600
I've discussed the
phenomenon of EIT, which is

01:05:25.600 --> 01:05:27.590
coherent population trapping.

01:05:27.590 --> 01:05:34.810
But there is an extension, which
is VSCPT, Velocity Selective

01:05:34.810 --> 01:05:39.880
Coherent Population Trapping,
and VSCPT was a powerful method

01:05:39.880 --> 01:05:43.300
to cool atoms below
the recoil limit,

01:05:43.300 --> 01:05:48.070
but I've not connected anything
of coherent population trapping

01:05:48.070 --> 01:05:49.080
with the Doppler shift.

01:05:49.080 --> 01:05:52.300
So for all this
discussion, please

01:05:52.300 --> 01:05:56.223
assume the atom is not moving.

01:05:56.223 --> 01:05:56.890
Other questions?

01:06:01.870 --> 01:06:10.810
Then let me just say a
few words about the fact

01:06:10.810 --> 01:06:18.850
that we have a large derivative
of the index of refraction,

01:06:18.850 --> 01:06:33.350
and this, of course,
is used for generating

01:06:33.350 --> 01:06:34.670
what is called slow light.

01:06:37.410 --> 01:06:47.000
The group velocity of light
is the speed of light,

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:49.290
but then it has a
denominator which

01:06:49.290 --> 01:06:52.002
is the derivative of
the index of refraction

01:06:52.002 --> 01:06:53.085
with respect to frequency.

01:07:01.770 --> 01:07:05.240
Towards the end of
the last century,

01:07:05.240 --> 01:07:10.110
there were predictions that
electromagnetically induced

01:07:10.110 --> 01:07:18.370
transparency would give you
very sharp features which can

01:07:18.370 --> 01:07:20.980
be used for very slow light.

01:07:25.610 --> 01:07:30.770
And what eventually triggered
major developments in the field

01:07:30.770 --> 01:07:38.230
was this landmark
paper by Lene Hau where

01:07:38.230 --> 01:07:41.410
she used the Bose-Einstein
condensate to eliminate

01:07:41.410 --> 01:07:43.290
all kinds of Doppler broadening.

01:07:43.290 --> 01:07:45.290
There are other tricks
how you can eliminate it,

01:07:45.290 --> 01:07:47.260
but this was the
most powerful way

01:07:47.260 --> 01:07:49.850
to just take a Bose-Einstein
condensate where

01:07:49.850 --> 01:08:00.880
atoms have no thermal velocity
and, in this research,

01:08:00.880 --> 01:08:03.970
she was able to show
that light propagated

01:08:03.970 --> 01:08:05.680
at the speed of a bicycle.

01:08:05.680 --> 01:08:09.020
So it was a dramatic reduction
of the speed of light,

01:08:09.020 --> 01:08:11.740
and this showed the
true potential of EIT.

01:08:11.740 --> 01:08:13.240
There have been
other demonstrations

01:08:13.240 --> 01:08:15.940
before where light has been
slowed by a factor of 100

01:08:15.940 --> 01:08:18.340
or a few hundred,
but eventually,

01:08:18.340 --> 01:08:21.740
combining that with a
Doppler-less feature

01:08:21.740 --> 01:08:25.010
because the atoms
don't move in a BEC

01:08:25.010 --> 01:08:26.790
created a dramatic effect.

01:08:31.850 --> 01:08:38.430
So we have now two
ways how we can get

01:08:38.430 --> 01:08:40.660
a large derivative, dn d omega.

01:08:40.660 --> 01:08:43.819
I've discussed here
the general case

01:08:43.819 --> 01:08:47.800
that we have a narrow feature,
a broad feature, because we

01:08:47.800 --> 01:08:55.750
have the coupling light
detuned from the excited state,

01:08:55.750 --> 01:09:07.810
but let me just point out that
even if you have the coupling

01:09:07.810 --> 01:09:15.680
light on resonance, depends
what you really want,

01:09:15.680 --> 01:09:23.410
but you can get an even
stronger feature in the index

01:09:23.410 --> 01:09:24.804
of refraction versus frequency.

01:09:31.270 --> 01:09:34.174
This is now the situation where
we have the strong absorption

01:09:34.174 --> 01:09:40.670
feature, but then we
have the EIT window.

01:09:40.670 --> 01:09:44.760
So we have this superposition
of a positive Lorentzian

01:09:44.760 --> 01:09:48.109
and a negative
Lorentzian, and if I now

01:09:48.109 --> 01:09:55.490
run it through my
Kramers-Kronig calculator

01:09:55.490 --> 01:09:57.700
and I take the
dispersive shape, I

01:09:57.700 --> 01:10:01.780
can sort of do it for the
broad feature in this way

01:10:01.780 --> 01:10:05.460
and for the narrow
feature in this way,

01:10:05.460 --> 01:10:07.760
and now you have
to add up the two.

01:10:07.760 --> 01:10:12.270
And what you realize
is at this point,

01:10:12.270 --> 01:10:21.390
you have a huge dn d omega.

01:10:21.390 --> 01:10:24.340
What I'm plotting here is on
the left side, the absorption

01:10:24.340 --> 01:10:28.290
of the Lorentzian, and you
can regard this sharp notch

01:10:28.290 --> 01:10:30.040
as a second Lorentzian.

01:10:30.040 --> 01:10:33.440
So you have the positive
Lorentzian, negative

01:10:33.440 --> 01:10:36.190
Lorentzian, and then you
take the dispersive features

01:10:36.190 --> 01:10:38.680
and you add them up
with the correct sign.

01:10:38.680 --> 01:10:44.180
So whether you're realizing now
for quite a general situation

01:10:44.180 --> 01:10:48.030
where you have single photon
detuning, which I discussed

01:10:48.030 --> 01:10:51.160
before, or whether you're on
the single photon resonance,

01:10:51.160 --> 01:10:55.550
you can have extremely
sharp features.

01:11:01.310 --> 01:11:03.630
So now you can take
it to the next level.

01:11:03.630 --> 01:11:06.970
You have a light pulse
which enters a medium,

01:11:06.970 --> 01:11:12.780
and now the light pulse slowly
moves through the medium.

01:11:12.780 --> 01:11:17.760
But while the light pulse
moves through the medium,

01:11:17.760 --> 01:11:20.894
you reduce the strength
of the coupling laser.

01:11:24.212 --> 01:11:25.160
What happens?

01:11:28.490 --> 01:11:32.380
So you do now an adiabatic
change of your system.

01:11:32.380 --> 01:11:40.840
You do an adiabatic change
of the control field

01:11:40.840 --> 01:11:55.020
omega 2 while the probe
pulse is in the medium.

01:11:55.020 --> 01:12:04.430
Well, that means that under
idealized assumptions which

01:12:04.430 --> 01:12:06.810
we've discussed, this
feature gets narrower

01:12:06.810 --> 01:12:08.800
and narrower and narrower.

01:12:08.800 --> 01:12:13.850
If omega 2 goes to 0, the
strength of the control field,

01:12:13.850 --> 01:12:17.250
this feature becomes
infinitesimally narrow.

01:12:17.250 --> 01:12:21.480
And therefore, this feature
becomes infinitely sharp,

01:12:21.480 --> 01:12:27.440
and that means that the
group velocity goes to zero.

01:12:31.210 --> 01:12:35.950
This is now in
the popular press,

01:12:35.950 --> 01:12:44.510
it's called stopped
light or frozen light

01:12:44.510 --> 01:12:46.960
because the light has
come to a standstill.

01:12:50.540 --> 01:12:54.450
What really happens
is the following.

01:12:54.450 --> 01:13:06.480
We have our coupling
laser, omega 2,

01:13:06.480 --> 01:13:10.600
and we have our
probe laser, omega 1.

01:13:10.600 --> 01:13:19.370
When we do what I just said is
that omega 2 goes through zero,

01:13:19.370 --> 01:13:26.840
then the dark state originally,
for very strong omega 2,

01:13:26.840 --> 01:13:33.590
remember the dark state was g?

01:13:33.590 --> 01:13:35.800
But now if we let
omega 2 go to zero,

01:13:35.800 --> 01:13:37.280
the dark state will become f.

01:13:43.420 --> 01:13:50.990
And that means that in a way,
every photon in the probe pulse

01:13:50.990 --> 01:13:55.820
has now pumped an atom from
g through two photon Raman

01:13:55.820 --> 01:13:57.940
process into f.

01:13:57.940 --> 01:14:00.650
So therefore, what it
means to stop light

01:14:00.650 --> 01:14:05.710
or to freeze light means simply
that the photons of the laser

01:14:05.710 --> 01:14:11.860
have turned into an atomic
excitation where the excitation

01:14:11.860 --> 01:14:14.270
is now the state, f.

01:14:14.270 --> 01:14:17.560
In other words, you
have written the photon.

01:14:17.560 --> 01:14:20.570
The photon has now put the
atom into a different hyperfine

01:14:20.570 --> 01:14:21.070
state.

01:14:23.840 --> 01:14:26.750
So if this is done
adiabatically,

01:14:26.750 --> 01:14:30.400
and I can't do full
justice in this course,

01:14:30.400 --> 01:14:35.420
but this means that
the light is coherently

01:14:35.420 --> 01:14:52.760
converted into the atomic--

01:14:55.600 --> 01:14:58.580
when I say "coherently"
say "into population," I

01:14:58.580 --> 01:15:01.940
mean all the quantum
phases, everything which

01:15:01.940 --> 01:15:06.470
was in the quantum nature of the
light has now been converted,

01:15:06.470 --> 01:15:08.450
has been written
into the state, f.

01:15:12.290 --> 01:15:17.720
This is often called, because
g and f are hyperfine states,

01:15:17.720 --> 01:15:20.880
this means that
you have coherently

01:15:20.880 --> 01:15:24.870
converted the photon or
the electromagnetic wave

01:15:24.870 --> 01:15:30.030
in the probe beam into
a spin wave or a magnon.

01:15:37.480 --> 01:15:40.910
Anyway, I just want to
show you the analogy.

01:15:40.910 --> 01:15:45.440
The fact that you can put the
quantum information of light

01:15:45.440 --> 01:15:47.930
into an atomic state
and back and forth,

01:15:47.930 --> 01:15:52.140
we've discussed that when we
had the situation of cavity QED.

01:15:52.140 --> 01:15:55.840
We prepared a superposition
of ground and excited state

01:15:55.840 --> 01:15:59.640
and exactly the same quantum
state which we had in the atom

01:15:59.640 --> 01:16:02.950
we later found in the
cavity as a superposition

01:16:02.950 --> 01:16:06.250
of the zero photon and
the one photon state.

01:16:06.250 --> 01:16:10.390
So from those general concepts,
it should be clear to you

01:16:10.390 --> 01:16:13.130
that it is possible
to coherently

01:16:13.130 --> 01:16:17.330
transform a quantum
state from light to atoms

01:16:17.330 --> 01:16:19.950
and back to light.

01:16:19.950 --> 01:16:22.300
And here you see the
different realization.

01:16:22.300 --> 01:16:28.530
We have a quantum state of
the photon in the probe laser,

01:16:28.530 --> 01:16:31.780
and we can now describe
the excitations

01:16:31.780 --> 01:16:37.340
in the system in a
parametrized way.

01:16:40.170 --> 01:16:43.650
What it means is for
the strong probe laser,

01:16:43.650 --> 01:16:48.120
for the strong coupling laser,
the excitation in the system

01:16:48.120 --> 01:16:51.550
travels as a photon
in the field one,

01:16:51.550 --> 01:16:56.810
but when you reduce the
coupling in the coupling laser,

01:16:56.810 --> 01:17:01.650
the excitation becomes
less and less photon-like.

01:17:01.650 --> 01:17:06.520
It becomes more and more
magnon-like, spin wave like.

01:17:06.520 --> 01:17:09.230
And the moment you reduce the
power in the coupling laser

01:17:09.230 --> 01:17:12.370
to zero, what used
to be an excitation

01:17:12.370 --> 01:17:16.330
in the electromagnetic field has
now been termed adiabatically

01:17:16.330 --> 01:17:20.015
into a spin excitation.

01:17:20.015 --> 01:17:23.660
Coherence has been written
into the hyperfine states

01:17:23.660 --> 01:17:25.629
or your atoms, g and f.

01:17:31.620 --> 01:17:34.900
All this is done coherently,
and therefore reversibly.

01:17:39.630 --> 01:17:50.500
You can read out the information
by simply time reversing

01:17:50.500 --> 01:17:52.480
the process.

01:17:52.480 --> 01:17:55.570
You ramp up again
the coupling laser,

01:17:55.570 --> 01:18:00.170
and that adiabatically turns
the spin excitation back

01:18:00.170 --> 01:18:02.580
into an excitation of the
electromagnetic field.

01:18:10.750 --> 01:18:11.520
Any questions?

01:18:20.830 --> 01:18:22.600
Well, we have
three minutes left,

01:18:22.600 --> 01:18:25.770
but I'm not getting
started with superradiance.

01:18:25.770 --> 01:18:28.070
We have one more
topic left, and this

01:18:28.070 --> 01:18:31.610
will be the topic on
Wednesday, decay superradiance,

01:18:31.610 --> 01:18:36.620
and this is when we discuss the
phenomenon of coherence where

01:18:36.620 --> 01:18:42.100
we have coherence not only in
one atom between two or three

01:18:42.100 --> 01:18:42.890
levels.

01:18:42.890 --> 01:18:45.040
We will then
discuss on Wednesday

01:18:45.040 --> 01:18:48.280
if we have coherence
between many atoms,

01:18:48.280 --> 01:18:51.480
and this at the heart
of superradiance.

01:18:51.480 --> 01:18:51.980
OK.

01:18:51.980 --> 01:18:54.130
See you on Wednesday.